    <h1><a name="title">Premailer Results</a></h1>
    <div class="body">
    <p>We&rsquo;ve processed <%= @source_description %>, and</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li>made all your CSS inline,</li>
      <li>changed relative links to absolute links,</li>
      <% unless @results[:options][:link_query_string].nil? or @results[:options][:link_query_string].empty? %><li>appended <tt>?<%= @results[:options][:link_query_string] %></tt> to your links,</li><% end %>
      <li>moved any CSS pseudo-classes (like <tt>:hover</tt>) to the <tt>&lt;head&gt;</tt>,</li>
      <li>checked your HTML and CSS for compatibiliy with e-mail programs, and</li>
      <li>created a plain-text version of your message</li>
   </ul>

    <div class="thanks meta">Time for some testing?<br>Campaign Monitor offers a thorough<br><a href="http://www.campaignmonitor.com/testing/">e-mail client testing service</a>.</div>


    <p>&#x00bb; <a href="<%= @results[:output][:html_file] %>" title="Contents of <%= @url %> with inline CSS">View the HTML results</a></p>

    <textarea cols="80" rows="5" id="html_output" class="premailer_output"><%= @results[:output][:html].to_xs %></textarea>

    <p>&#x00bb; <a href="<%= @results[:output][:txt_file] %>" title="Contents of <%= @url %> converted to plain text">View the plain-text results</a></p>

    <textarea cols="80" rows="5" id="txt_output" class="premailer_output"><%= @results[:output][:txt] %></textarea>

    <script type="text/javascript">
    <%  action_label = @source_description == 'your HTML content' ? 'Uploaded HTML' : 'Remote file' %>
    try {
      pageTracker._trackEvent("Premailer", "Processed", "<%= action_label %>");

    } catch(err) {} 
    </script>
    
<% if @results[:warnings] %>
<br>
  <h3>HTML and CSS warnings</h3>

  <% if @results[:warnings].length > 0 %>

  <p>Warnings are generated from several sources, including the <a href="http://www.email-standards.org/">Email Standards Project&rsquo;s guides</a>.</p>

  

  <table class="warnings" id="premailer-warnings" summary="List of HTML and CSS warnings">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Property</th>
      <th>Support</th>
      <th>Unsupported clients</th>
    </tr>
    <tbody>
    <% @results[:warnings].each do |w| %>
    <tr class="<%= w[:level].downcase %>">
      <td class="property"><%= w[:message] %></td>
      <td class="level"><%= w[:level].capitalize %></td>
      <td><%= w[:clients] %></td>
    </tr>
    <% end %>
    </tbody>
  </table>
<% else %>
<p>None.</p>
<% end %>
<% end %>
</div>